n<li><a href=\"https://youtu.be/G_V_5a-J9Us?si=Mo2Rv0WbSVqngEaP\">Ten Weird Writing Tips That Actually Work - YouTube</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://youtu.be/mzj91fYrUL0?si=xgKpCC3Dy8UHx3s1\">Why I love Obsidian for writing novels and fiction worldbuilding - YouTube</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://youtu.be/kfyA1UTo1sI?si=QL1fpUVb9cJTE-L9\">Fantasy fiction writing using Obsidian - A discussion with Eleanor Konik - YouTube</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"plotting--outlining-methods\">Plotting &#x26; Outlining Methods<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#plotting--outlining-methods\"></a></h2>\n<h3 id=\"27-chapter-\">27-Chapter üíñ<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#27-chapter-\"></a></h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://youtu.be/fe3eodLF_Uo?si=MfcHf4wfuH48k2rH\">HOW TO OUTLINE - 3 act 9 block 27 chapter example - YouTube</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://youtu.be/Y3wua1KWRVI?si=G-2ucsHFfqh4WsGA\">The Ultimate Guide to Outlining Your Story: Exploring the 27-Chapter Outline, From Kat O'Keeffe - YouTube</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://youtu.be/RNV--FikzF0?si=zHBcy_JinlNZ-zwr\">The Ultimate Guide to Outlining Your Story: Exploring the 27-Chapter Outline‚ÄîUPDATED - YouTube</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"save-the-cat\">Save the Cat<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#save-the-cat\"></a></h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://youtu.be/k8EfEEjbwGk?si=-Q1TkAttNqhammJx\">How to Write a Novel in 15 Steps with the Save the Cat! Beat Sheet - YouTube</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"dialogue\">Dialogue<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#dialogue\"></a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://youtu.be/-AhtKvgy6MA?si=U9XBRzot0MdRcWCh\">The Key to Writing Freakishly Good Dialogue - Video Essay - YouTube</a>\n<ul>\n<li>summarize important info <strong>FIRST</strong></li>\n<li>characters speak through <strong>FILTERS</strong></li>\n<li>know the <strong>personality</strong> of your characters, even the minor ones</li>\n<li>every piece of dialogue should have a <strong>purpose</strong> and a <strong>goal</strong></li>\n<li>disagreement =/ conflict; use the plot to <strong>trigger</strong> conflict</li>\n<li><strong>allegories</strong> are great ways to have dialogue</li>\n<li>‚Äúyes, and‚Ä¶‚Äù is also helpful</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://youtu.be/-e5Y2yH7RhQ?si=BeHzSF7Z0vsY77C8\">Dialogue Mistakes New Writers Make ‚ùå¬†Avoid These Cringeworthy Cliches!! - YouTube</a>\n<ul>\n<li>characters <strong>don‚Äôt</strong> know exactly how they‚Äôre feeling, so <strong>they don‚Äôt tell you</strong></li>\n<li>do use <em>subtext</em> and <strong>show</strong> readers what the character is feeling</li>\n<li><strong>script format</strong> might be helpful for your first manuscript</li>\n<li>don‚Äôt make all your characters <strong>sound</strong> the same (grammar, slang, canter, etc.)</li>\n<li>don‚Äôt overuse <a title=\"Private\" href=\"https://wiki.dendron.so/notes/hfyvYGJZQiUwQaaxQO27q.html\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"private\">dialogue tags (Private)</a></li>\n<li>keep your dialogue fast-paced &#x26; to the point</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>","noteIndex":{"id":"root","title":"Yoela's Garden","desc":"","updated":1728743963747,"created":1595961348801,"custom":{"nav_order":0,"permalink":"/"},"fname":"root","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":".","selfContained":true,"name":"Dendron"},"contentHash":"ae2a8a5da1925caba2d4a39ffbc7d28f","links":[],"anchors":{},"children":["wsv54z6fb6pyr9l8y3kv8li","36im6j46cxlgm7yqwfsy0sy","tqb5hhhvpbz2nzpykihc7l2","cyzf7ekzgc9m43pfwa3kv5e"],"parent":null,"data":{},"body":"\nWelcome to my digital garden! What's that? Well, a digital garden is a curated set of notes, often shared online for learning and sharing purposes. My garden is mostly full of my study notes, plain ole' random notes, prose, and whatever world I'm creating at the moment. So, yes, I'm tending to it nearly every day.\n\nWith that out of the way, just a fair warning, not 